- Hi, you.
- Hello.

31:34.184 --> 31:36.186
Are you new around here?

31:38.021 --> 31:39.523
Yeah.

31:39.898 --> 31:41.024
Brand-new.

31:41.191 --> 31:43.660
Oh. Welcome.

31:43.819 --> 31:45.162
Well, thanks.

32:44.004 --> 32:45.347
Hello, Grandma.

32:52.512 --> 32:54.185
Did I miss the parade?

32:55.807 --> 32:57.059
What parade?

32:57.225 --> 33:00.024
You know, the one that usually
arrives before you do.

33:00.437 --> 33:02.155
That nice tour manager...

33:02.689 --> 33:05.818
and all those bodyguards
and the reporters.

33:06.526 --> 33:08.244
No. It's just me this time.

33:09.905 --> 33:13.500
I hardly recognized you without
all that hair. Ha, ha.

33:21.791 --> 33:23.043
Oh, yeah?

33:23.543 --> 33:25.170
- Did you quit?
- No.

33:26.213 --> 33:28.090
It's just a short pause.

33:31.134 --> 33:33.853
- So how are you?
- Oh, hell, I'm fine.

33:34.721 --> 33:38.521
I'd like to quit. It's just
getting bigger and bigger.

33:39.559 --> 33:43.063
- Starting to look like a circus.
- I saw you over in Dallas.

33:43.563 --> 33:47.033
- That was quite an extravaganza.
- Why didn't you call me?

33:47.192 --> 33:50.366
I'd have got you tickets and you
could've been backstage with me.

33:50.529 --> 33:51.906
You were working.

33:52.113 --> 33:54.707
You don't disturb men
when they're working.

33:54.866 --> 33:57.244
- Did you like it?
- Of course I did.

33:57.702 --> 33:59.420
It was you singing.

34:00.705 --> 34:02.582
I love to hear you sing.

34:03.208 --> 34:07.588
- But...
- It was loud, and I couldn't hear the words.

34:07.921 --> 34:10.389
Without the words, there's no song.

34:11.132 --> 34:12.304
And?

34:12.926 --> 34:15.600
I could've done without
the smoke and the lights.

34:15.762 --> 34:18.356
- Yeah, me too.
- But the kids liked it.

34:27.482 --> 34:30.031
- You kept my old guitar.
- Yeah.

34:40.745 --> 34:42.918
I learned to play on this old Dove.

34:44.958 --> 34:46.130
Yeah.

34:46.710 --> 34:50.635
I kept it around in case you might
want to play me a song sometime.

34:52.382 --> 34:54.304
No smoke. No lights.

34:54.926 --> 34:56.428
No amplifiers.

34:57.220 --> 34:59.848
No big-stage production.
Just me and my guitar.

35:00.015 --> 35:02.939
- Think anybody would buy that?
- I would.

35:17.032 --> 35:19.330
Bye, Grandma. I'll see you soon.

37:11.896 --> 37:12.943
Howdy.

37:13.565 --> 37:14.862
Want a beer?

37:15.400 --> 37:17.118
Yeah, I'll take a beer.

37:29.831 --> 37:32.004
Is there a rent-car place
anywhere nearby?

37:33.209 --> 37:34.882
Where you trying to get?

37:35.211 --> 37:36.929
Louisiana. Shreveport.

37:39.090 --> 37:40.262
Here.

37:44.846 --> 37:48.646
I used to play in here years ago,
back when I was in high school.

37:49.309 --> 37:51.311
Yeah, I know who you are.

37:52.604 --> 37:54.527
- You do?
- Yes, sir.

37:55.607 --> 37:57.609
I tell you, the place
hasn't changed much.

37:58.735 --> 38:01.204
No. No.

38:02.030 --> 38:05.500
If you played here, you earned
this. It's on the house.

38:06.409 --> 38:07.877
Thank you.

38:08.036 --> 38:10.880
There is a General rent-a-car
place just down the road.

38:11.039 --> 38:13.667
Okay. Appreciate it.

39:25.697 --> 39:30.954
<i>My friends, Shreveport, Louisiana
welcomes Dusty in concert.</i>

39:52.515 --> 39:54.313
Dave, come in. Anything?

39:55.143 --> 39:57.942
<i>Nothing, Lula. We have all
the entrances watched.</i>

40:04.652 --> 40:06.950
I'm too old for this.

40:11.951 --> 40:14.045
Hey, we can't hear it, man.

40:21.753 --> 40:24.677
Will somebody please
tell me where he is?

40:26.049 --> 40:27.596
Put that thing away.

40:30.386 --> 40:32.138
One of you must know.

40:33.765 --> 40:37.144
- Earl?
- How many times you gonna ask me?

40:38.478 --> 40:41.197
All right. All right, look.

40:43.191 --> 40:45.489
Dusty and I had a
fight the other day.

40:46.402 --> 40:48.780
And I said some things
I shouldn't have.

40:49.822 --> 40:51.244
And I'm sorry.

40:52.617 --> 40:57.043
But I can't apologize to him until
one of you tells me where he is!

40:57.538 --> 41:01.338
- Are you cancelling the show?
- No, I'm not cancelling the show.

41:01.751 --> 41:03.845
There are 25,000 fans out there.

41:04.462 --> 41:07.181
Some of them drove hundreds
of miles to get here.

41:07.340 --> 41:09.468
And they're gonna get their show.

41:14.681 --> 41:16.308
He'll be here.

41:17.600 --> 41:19.352
Thanks, gentlemen.

41:20.019 --> 41:22.522
Y'all been a real big help.

41:22.855 --> 41:25.529
You're supposed to be out on
that stage in five minutes.

41:25.692 --> 41:29.071
I suggest if you wanna keep your
jobs, you better get out there.

41:35.159 --> 41:37.958
<i>Dusty! Dusty! Dusty!</i>

41:46.212 --> 41:47.429
Dave.

41:50.842 --> 41:52.435
Let's do it.

41:53.052 --> 41:54.144
Dusty?

41:54.303 --> 41:56.806
<i>Dusty! Dusty! Dusty!</i>

42:03.271 --> 42:05.023
Bring the lights
down really slowly.

42:08.067 --> 42:10.445
More smoke. Now. Right now.

42:16.909 --> 42:18.286
I think we got it.

42:19.120 --> 42:21.464
Okay. Good.

42:22.206 --> 42:25.460
<i>When you hear twin fiddles
And a steel guitar</i>

42:28.588 --> 42:32.309
<i>You're listening to the sound
Of the American heart</i>

42:33.926 --> 42:36.429
<i>And Opry music on a Saturday night</i>

42:36.596 --> 42:40.772
<i>Brings a smile to your face
And a tear to your eye</i>

42:52.528 --> 42:53.905
Whoo!

45:00.990 --> 45:03.584
- Harley, honey. How about a little dance?
- Not now, Al.

45:03.743 --> 45:06.246
Oh, come on. Why are you
always avoiding me?

45:52.458 --> 45:54.210
- Where are you going?
- I'm going home.

45:54.377 --> 45:56.630
- Oh, come on.
- Al, leave me alone!

46:04.387 --> 46:06.731
- Hold on. Where you going?
- I'm going home.

46:06.889 --> 46:09.642
- Come on back in.
- I don't want to. I'm going home.

46:10.101 --> 46:11.978
I don't like you. Leave me alone!

46:12.144 --> 46:14.317
- Leave her alone.
- What do you want?

46:14.480 --> 46:17.074
- No, Al! Don't!
- You better back off, cowboy!

46:17.233 --> 46:20.328
- Come on, there's no need to do this!
- I said, back off!

46:20.486 --> 46:21.988
Leave him alone.

46:22.154 --> 46:23.326
Al, come on.

46:23.489 --> 46:25.992
- You're bothering the lady.
- No, don't!

46:26.409 --> 46:29.583
Al, no! Al, that's enough!

46:30.496 --> 46:32.874
God! Why does he
always do this to me?

46:34.667 --> 46:35.884
Al, stop it!

46:36.043 --> 46:38.387
- Hell, he started it.
- Leave him alone. Stop it.

46:38.546 --> 46:41.516
- You should've stayed inside.
- Leave him alone. That's enough!

46:42.174 --> 46:46.350
- Stop it, now. Just stop it!
- Come on back in. Come on back in, now.

46:46.512 --> 46:47.684
Ahh! Ahh!

46:47.847 --> 46:50.521
Harley, my hand! My hand!

46:51.100 --> 46:53.194
- Watch your hands!
- Open the door! Ohh!

46:53.352 --> 46:55.525
Oh, my nose!

46:56.939 --> 47:00.318
- Sorry. I'm sorry about your nose.
- Leave me alone, Harley!

47:00.568 --> 47:03.663
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry. It was a mistake.
- Leave me alone.

47:05.072 --> 47:07.370
Why is this happening to me?

47:20.129 --> 47:24.054
<i>I'm not afraid to go
You bet I'm not</i>

47:24.884 --> 47:28.889
<i>Where the side walk
ends, you left a lot</i>

47:29.722 --> 47:33.818
<i>Where the sidewalk ends
And the road begins</i>

47:34.560 --> 47:39.236
<i>We said goodbye on
a cold dark night</i>

47:39.690 --> 47:43.536
<i>I'm not afraid to go
You bet I'm not</i>

47:44.236 --> 47:48.241
<i>Where the side walk
ends, you left a lot</i>

47:49.116 --> 47:53.622
<i>Where the side walk
ends, you left a lot</i>

47:53.996 --> 47:59.002
<i>Where the side walk
ends, you left a lot</i>

48:02.088 --> 48:05.683
Kill spot. Kill it.
Listen to me! Kill spot.

48:28.280 --> 48:30.624
- Bobby.
- Nice show, Lula.

48:30.908 --> 48:31.955
Thanks.

48:32.118 --> 48:35.713
When's Dusty gonna be ready to give
me the rest of that interview?

48:35.871 --> 48:38.670
I've got a plane to catch
in about two hours.

48:38.833 --> 48:41.211
I'm not gonna let Dusty
do the interview tonight.

48:41.377 --> 48:44.381
He's been fighting a sore throat
and I just wanna keep him quiet.

48:44.547 --> 48:47.676
Come on. I just got a couple
of questions. It's no big deal.

48:48.300 --> 48:50.644
Hey, Lula, it's a good show, huh?

48:51.303 --> 48:54.477
Can't do it. My first
responsibility is to Dusty.

48:55.558 --> 48:56.684
I gotta go.

48:57.184 --> 48:59.403
- Wait a minute.
- Sam.

48:59.687 --> 49:02.281
I want you to take Mr.
Louis to the airport.

49:02.440 --> 49:04.863
See he's taken care of.
Catch you in Vegas, okay?

49:05.025 --> 49:07.995
You are really starting
to wear me slick.

49:08.446 --> 49:12.542
We're not playing games. Get in the
bus before somebody sees your face.

49:12.950 --> 49:14.668
What the hell you doing?

49:14.827 --> 49:17.876
- I'm going in this bus.
- No, that's Dusty's bus.

49:18.831 --> 49:20.549
Well, tonight, I'm Dusty.

49:21.250 --> 49:24.003
You don't want my fans to
get suspicious, do you?

49:25.129 --> 49:26.847
You don't belong in there.

49:30.342 --> 49:33.186
Lula, you better get over here.
We have a problem.

49:39.602 --> 49:40.649
Peckerhead.

49:53.908 --> 49:56.957
Well, what do you think?

49:58.204 --> 50:01.708
Buddy, we were real lucky. If there
was one glitch with the tape...

50:01.874 --> 50:04.878
- if Bobby Louis had come much closer...
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

50:07.338 --> 50:09.591
Hell, aren't you
even gonna thank me?

50:10.633 --> 50:11.885
Yes.

50:12.176 --> 50:14.224
Yes, of course, I am.

50:14.386 --> 50:17.185
- Thank you.
- Good. Then we can...

50:17.348 --> 50:18.895
We can go celebrate.

50:23.437 --> 50:24.484
Lula.

50:25.439 --> 50:28.613
The guys in the band would
like to have a word with you.

50:38.160 --> 50:40.913
Get him out of these clothes
before someone sees him.

50:41.080 --> 50:42.878
You bet.

50:43.749 --> 50:45.296
Ah, hell.

50:46.752 --> 50:48.254
You guys were great tonight.

50:48.420 --> 50:50.923
What the hell was Buddy
Jackson doing out there?

50:51.090 --> 50:54.765
Why didn't you just cancel the
show, rain check it or something?

50:54.927 --> 50:56.975
We can't play with a guy
who's lip-synching.

50:57.137 --> 51:00.767
If we speed up or slow down, he can't
follow us or the audience will know.

51:00.933 --> 51:02.276
Where is Dusty, anyway?

51:02.434 --> 51:05.108
Buddy Jackson? Have you
lost your mind, Lula?

51:05.271 --> 51:07.319
If I hadn't done what I did...

51:07.773 --> 51:10.276
all of those people would
have gone home mad.

51:10.442 --> 51:11.739
And we...

51:11.902 --> 51:13.825
would all be out of a job.

51:14.446 --> 51:17.165
Now, I am sure that
your ex-wives...

51:17.324 --> 51:19.998
and Henry's five kids
and Keith's mother...

51:20.160 --> 51:22.788
don't care if it was
Buddy, Dusty...

51:23.372 --> 51:28.003
or King Kong up there on that stage,
so long as you get your paychecks.

51:28.168 --> 51:32.298
You know I have always
taken care of you guys.

51:33.799 --> 51:34.891
Now...

51:35.134 --> 51:38.513
we've got a little time off before
we get to the big show in Vegas.

51:39.888 --> 51:43.483
Everything will be
straightened out.

51:46.103 --> 51:47.696
Dusty will be back.

51:49.148 --> 51:53.824
I'm gonna tell you something. I need you
to promise me you will not say one word...

51:53.986 --> 51:56.409
to anybody about what
happened tonight.

51:57.156 --> 51:58.874
This is for Dusty's sake.

52:00.409 --> 52:02.878
- And your own.
- For Dusty's sake?

52:03.370 --> 52:05.464
I'm sick to death of your crap.

52:07.416 --> 52:10.044
You had him hung up and
twisting in the wind.

52:11.503 --> 52:14.848
He had nothing to do with this.
Tonight was all you, Lula.

52:15.007 --> 52:17.009
He had nothing to do with this?

52:17.676 --> 52:18.893
He walked out.

52:19.053 --> 52:23.229
And he left you and me and everyone
in this room sitting on their thumbs.

52:23.432 --> 52:27.187
- He had everything to do with it.
- You should have cancelled tonight.

52:28.187 --> 52:31.236
I ain't gonna be a damn dancing
chicken in your freak show.

52:32.024 --> 52:33.901
Get yourself another drummer.

52:34.360 --> 52:35.612
Earl.

52:37.780 --> 52:38.872
Hey, Earl.

52:40.324 --> 52:41.746
Let's do it.

52:42.785 --> 52:44.708
Why the hell not?

53:41.677 --> 53:44.601
- What day is this?
- Friday.

53:45.639 --> 53:47.812
Oh, my. The show.

53:52.229 --> 53:55.483
- You know horses?
- I know a few.

54:07.453 --> 54:08.955
I'm sorry. I was...

54:09.997 --> 54:11.840
a little drunk last night.

54:11.999 --> 54:13.296
Yes, you were.

54:15.794 --> 54:17.011
My name's Wyatt.

54:18.255 --> 54:19.677
Wyatt.

54:22.551 --> 54:23.928
Well, Wyatt...

54:24.470 --> 54:25.847
you can't drink.

54:27.848 --> 54:29.850
And you can't fight.

54:31.560 --> 54:33.187
Can you eat?

54:35.689 --> 54:37.032
Yeah, I think so.

54:38.275 --> 54:42.121
Okay. Might as well
have some breakfast.

54:42.613 --> 54:44.240
Before you go.

54:50.746 --> 54:52.043
Well, come on.

54:57.002 --> 54:58.049
Excuse me.

55:02.424 --> 55:04.051
You can sit over there.

55:30.536 --> 55:32.630
Sure do appreciate
your hospitality.

55:40.212 --> 55:41.259
The hat.

56:01.358 --> 56:02.826
Sure is good.

56:14.371 --> 56:19.628
Harley. You were nearly three seconds
long on that pattern this morning.

56:22.546 --> 56:24.298
I got in late.

56:25.757 --> 56:29.102
Maybe you should just get in a
little bit earlier, you know.

56:31.930 --> 56:34.228
We all need to win this time.

57:21.813 --> 57:23.893
- Hey, Harley.
- What are you doing here?

57:23.982 --> 57:26.952
- What are you doing here?
- I felt bad... Don't be like that.

57:27.110 --> 57:31.081
Why do you have to start this all the
time? Go back in the truck, go home!

57:31.239 --> 57:33.992
Who was that fella last night?
I've never seen him around.

57:34.159 --> 57:35.411
None of your business.

57:35.577 --> 57:38.080
It's not like you know him or
something. What's the deal?

57:38.246 --> 57:41.170
What right do you have to tell
me what I can and can't do! Go!

57:41.333 --> 57:45.008
- You made a mess out of me last night.
- Excuse me.

57:45.671 --> 57:48.470
Why don't you just shoot me
and put me out of my misery.

57:48.632 --> 57:52.262
- I'm sorry about that.
- It's okay, it's not about my nose.

57:52.427 --> 57:55.601
I don't want you coming here and
telling me what I can and can't do.

57:55.764 --> 57:59.860
- I am not telling you what to do.
- You do it all the time! I'm tired of it!

58:00.018 --> 58:02.862
- How long have we known one another?
- Don't you start that.

58:03.021 --> 58:04.694
I'm not starting nothing.

58:04.856 --> 58:07.109
- You all right?
- I'm fine.

58:07.275 --> 58:08.948
Just go back in the
house. Go ahead.

58:10.862 --> 58:14.162
Yeah. Don't you remember that
beating you got last night?

58:14.324 --> 58:18.204
Me? You look like the one
who took the beating.

58:18.829 --> 58:21.082
Not by you. I whupped your ass.

58:21.373 --> 58:23.296
- Oh, really?
- Yeah, really.

58:23.458 --> 58:25.881
What's the matter? Were
you too drunk to notice?

58:26.044 --> 58:28.638
Stop it! Just stop it! Stop it!

58:30.257 --> 58:34.262
Now, we were all drunk last night,
and I'm sure we're all sorry.

58:34.720 --> 58:36.722
Come on, Al, get in
your truck and go home.

58:36.888 --> 58:40.267
Me? Why should I?
This drunk is staying.

58:40.434 --> 58:43.938
- Look, Harley, honey...
- The lady said to leave.

58:44.646 --> 58:48.276
Boy, you're just begging for
another ass-whupping, aren't you?

58:48.525 --> 58:49.777
Absolutely.

58:54.281 --> 58:58.787
What're you doing? What're you doing?
Just go back in the house. Go!

58:58.952 --> 59:01.296
- Oh, my nose!
- Go back in the house.

59:01.455 --> 59:02.832
My nose!

59:02.998 --> 59:04.420
Just go!

59:05.000 --> 59:08.095
Ahh! My hand! Oh, God!

59:10.672 --> 59:13.425
- Come on.
- It's busted up right now.

59:15.385 --> 59:17.308
He busted my nose again.

59:20.265 --> 59:21.767
Get my hat.

59:49.961 --> 59:51.679
Sure is a beautiful ranch.

59:58.804 --> 01:00:00.602
About how many acres y'all got?

01:00:21.952 --> 01:00:25.126
Yeah, I can't blame you
for keeping quiet.

01:00:25.872 --> 01:00:28.967
Kind of hard to get a word in
edgewise with those three.

01:00:32.170 --> 01:00:33.422
Yes, sir.

01:00:33.588 --> 01:00:36.592
People talk too darn
much for my taste.

01:00:37.926 --> 01:00:40.975
Yapping about this and that
when they ought to be...

01:00:41.138 --> 01:00:42.936
eating, working or sleeping.

01:00:43.098 --> 01:00:46.898
What's anybody say that everybody
doesn't already know anyway?

01:00:47.352 --> 01:00:51.073
- Can you tell me that?
- No, sir, I can't.

01:00:51.231 --> 01:00:54.861
That's too bad. Take,
for example, this morning.

01:00:55.861 --> 01:00:59.331
Now, we all know that Harley
was slow on her ride.

01:01:00.323 --> 01:01:04.044
We know she was out late last night.
That's no front-page news.

01:01:04.369 --> 01:01:06.087
So why talk about it?

01:01:11.918 --> 01:01:14.387
I guess I see what you're saying.

01:01:15.630 --> 01:01:18.850
You guess? Never guess.

01:01:19.342 --> 01:01:22.391
You got to know. I mean you got
to know what you're doing.

01:01:22.846 --> 01:01:26.521
If you guess, you're leaving
yourself wide open to suggestion.

01:01:26.683 --> 01:01:29.778
And that, to my mind, is what's
wrong with this whole country.

01:01:29.936 --> 01:01:32.030
I mean it's going straight to hell.

01:01:33.315 --> 01:01:35.693
Everybody's open to suggestion.

01:01:40.363 --> 01:01:43.458
Well, you coming or are
you just gonna sit there?

01:01:58.840 --> 01:02:02.765
- How long've you known Harley?
- Not very long.

01:02:04.638 --> 01:02:06.311
- Thousand.
- Pardon?

01:02:06.890 --> 01:02:09.518
- Uh, thousand acres.
- Oh.

01:02:10.685 --> 01:02:12.403
Used to be more.

01:02:12.729 --> 01:02:15.323
- What happened?
- Well...

01:02:15.982 --> 01:02:20.158
Getting to be a business. I'm a rancher.
I don't want to be a businessman.

01:02:20.445 --> 01:02:23.324
And taxes are getting
harder to pay.

01:02:23.698 --> 01:02:25.496
People want to buy us out.

01:02:25.784 --> 01:02:29.414
Seems like we wind up
selling it off, bit by bit.

01:02:29.746 --> 01:02:34.752
I'm kind of glad I won't be around
long enough to see it all go.

01:02:34.918 --> 01:02:35.965
And Harley?

01:02:36.211 --> 01:02:41.468
Well, Harley thinks she's going to
save it by winning at the rodeo.

01:02:49.391 --> 01:02:51.393
Would you excuse us
for a minute, please?

01:03:16.543 --> 01:03:18.045
You rope pretty good.

01:03:19.296 --> 01:03:21.515
I've always wanted to
learn how to do that.

01:03:21.673 --> 01:03:25.223
- Good luck.
- Any chance you'd give me some lessons?

01:03:25.385 --> 01:03:31.233
Ha, ha, ha. J.W. Did you hear that? This
guy wants us to give him roping lessons.

